ttom of the customer checkout page for your store. This         requires two separate browser tabs to be open.<br /><div class="imagecenter"><img class="image imagecenter" src="Tasks/img/Add%20Domain%20-%20Add%20existing%20domain.PNG" alt="Existing Domain" /></div><br /></p></shortdesc><topicmeta><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="adding_store_policies"></resourceid><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Adding Store Policies</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Adding Store Policies</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Policies are essential so that your customers know how you handle refunds, privacy,         and terms of service for transactions. Store policies are added on a different webpage but         will be displayed as links at the bottom of the customer checkout page for your store. This         requires two separate browser tabs to be open.<image align="center" alt="Existing Domain" class="- topic/image " href="img/Add%20Domain%20-%20Add%20existing%20domain.PNG" placement="break" scalefit="yes"></image></shortdesc><author class="- topic/author ">Ryan Ewaskiew, Jason Figueroa, Carter Francis, Mailie Liu</author></topicmeta></topic><topic href="Tasks/add_menu_and_links_to_store.html" data-id="add_menu_and_links_to_store" wh-toc-id="add_menu_and_links_to_store-d62e95"><title>Add a menu and links to your store</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc">With how prevalent social media and the use of other sites are in today's day and age, you’ll likely want to link external sites and accounts to your Shopify storefront.</p></shortdesc><topicmeta><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="add_menu_and_links_to_store"></resourceid><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Add a menu and links to your store</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Add a menu and links to your store</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">With how prevalent social media and the use of other sites are in today's day and age, you’ll likely want to link external sites and accounts to your Shopify storefront.</shortdesc><author class="- topic/author ">Ryan Ewaskiew, Jason Figueroa, Carter Francis, Mailie Liu</author></topicmeta></topic><topic href="Tasks/adding_products.html" data-id="adding_products" wh-toc-id="adding_products-d62e108"><title>Adding Products</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc"></p></shortdesc><topicmeta><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="adding_products"></resourceid><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Adding Products</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Adding Products</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc "></shortdesc><author class="- topic/author ">Ryan Ewaskiew, Jason Figueroa, Carter Francis, Mailie Liu</author></topicmeta></topic><topic href="Tasks/organizing_products.html" data-id="organizing_products" wh-toc-id="organizing_products-d62e120"><title>Organizing Products</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc">Shopify allows you to create product collections to organize your products; however,         you’d like through the use of collections. Examples of categories: Clothes for men, women,         or children Items on sale Items of a certain type, size or color Seasonal         products.</p></shortdesc><topicmeta><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="organizing_products"></resourceid><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Organizing Products</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Organizing Products</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Shopify allows you to create product collections to organize your products; however,         you’d like through the use of collections. Examples of categories: Clothes for men, women,         or children Items on sale Items of a certain type, size or color Seasonal         products.</shortdesc><author class="- topic/author ">Ryan Ewaskiew, Jason Figueroa, Carter Francis, Mailie Liu</author></topicmeta></topic><topic href="Concepts/customizing_a_theme.html" data-id="customizing_a_theme" wh-toc-id="customizing_a_theme-d62e133"><title>Customizing a Theme</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc"></p></shortdesc><topicmeta><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="customizing_a_theme"></resourceid><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Customizing a Theme</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Customizing a Theme</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc "></shortdesc><author class="- topic/author ">Ryan Ewaskiew, Jason Figueroa, Carter Francis, Mailie Liu</author></topicmeta></topic></topic><topic href="Concepts/domains.html" data-id="what_is_a_domain" wh-toc-id="what_is_a_domain-d62e145"><title>Domains</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc">Now that you have your store setup, you will need a way to show this store to your         customers. A domain will allow people to access your store through the internet. </p></shortdesc><topicmeta><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="what_is_a_domain"></resourceid><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Domains</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Domains</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Now that you have your store setup, you will need a way to show this store to your         customers. A domain will allow people to access your store through the internet. </shortdesc><author class="- topic/author ">Ryan Ewaskiew, Jason Figueroa, Carter Francis, Mailie Liu</author></topicmeta><topic href="Tasks/domain_through_shopify.html" data-id="domain_through_shopify" wh-toc-id="domain_through_shopify-d62e158"><title>Domain Through Shopify</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc">Shopify can host your online store through either a third-party domain or one that’s been bought from us.</p></shortdesc><topicmeta><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="domain_through_shopify"></resourceid><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Domain Through Shopify</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Domain Through Shopify</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Shopify can host your online store through either a third-party domain or one that’s been bought from us.</shortdesc><author class="- topic/author ">Ryan Ewaskiew, Jason Figueroa, Carter Francis, Mailie Liu</author></topicmeta></topic><topic href="Tasks/add_existing_domain.html" data-id="add_existing_domain" wh-toc-id="add_existing_domain-d62e171"><title>Add Existing Domain</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc">Shopify also allows you to add existing domains from third party providers. If you'd         instead do that than purchasing one of Shopify's, here are the steps in doing         so.</p></shortdesc><topicmeta><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="add_existing_domain"></resourceid><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Add Existing Domain</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Add Existing Domain</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Shopify also allows you to add existing domains from third party providers. If you'd         instead do that than purchasing one of Shopify's, here are the steps in doing         so.</shortdesc><author class="- topic/author ">Ryan Ewaskiew, Jason Figueroa, Carter Francis, Mailie Liu</author></topicmeta></topic><topic href="Tasks/setting_up_your_existing_domain_to_connect_to_shopify.html" data-id="setting_up_your_existing_domain_to_connect_to_shopify" wh-toc-id="setting_up_your_existing_domain_to_connect_to_shopify-d62e184"><title>Setting up your existing domain to connect to Shopify</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc">Shopify gives you the option to add in your own domain if it already exists. </p></shortdesc><topicmeta><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="setting_up_your_existing_domain_to_connect_to_shopify"></resourceid><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Setting up your existing domain to connect to Shopify</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Setting up your existing domain to connect to Shopify</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc ">Shopify gives you the option to add in your own domain if it already exists. </shortdesc><author class="- topic/author ">Ryan Ewaskiew, Jason Figueroa, Carter Francis, Mailie Liu</author></topicmeta></topic><topic href="Tasks/verify_shopify_connection.html" data-id="verify_shopify_connection" wh-toc-id="verify_shopify_connection-d62e197"><title>Verify Shopify Connection</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc"></p></shortdesc><topicmeta><resourceid class="- topic/resourceid " oxy-source="topic" appid="verify_shopify_connection"></resourceid><navtitle class="- topic/navtitle ">Verify Shopify Connection</navtitle><?ditaot gentext?><linktext class="- map/linktext ">Verify Shopify Connection</linktext><?ditaot genshortdesc?><shortdesc class="- map/shortdesc "></shortdesc><author class="- topic/author ">Ryan Ewaskiew, Jason Figueroa, Carter Francis, Mailie Liu</author></topicmeta></topic><topic href="Tasks/set_your_primary_domain.html" data-id="set_your_primary_domain" wh-toc-id="set_your_primary_domain-d62e209"><title>Set your primary domain</title><shortdesc><p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc">The primary domain of your storefront is the domain name that customers see in the browser’s address bar.</p><